  "body": "### Description\n\nSince smallrye-config, and quarkus support multiple profiles. It would be nice if the annotation ` @IfBuildProfile` would work the same way.\r\n\r\nWe can start the application with `-Dquarkus.profile=dev,foo`, smallrye will understand that there are two profiles dev and foo, but ` @IfBuildProfile` will see \"dev,foo\" as one profile, which makes it hard/impossible to restrict bean to a single of the profile.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n- ` @IfBuildProfile` could be repeatable as `@IfBuildProperty`\r\n- should split the profiles via the comma\r\n- should activate if one matches example if my class has `@IfBuildProfile(\"foo\")` if I start with profiles=dev,foo; it should work.\r\n  - otherwise  `@IfBuildProfile(\"foo\")`  and `@IfBuildProfile(\"dev\")` should be used ",
